# Commit Standards

## Format

```
type(TASK-XXX): short description

Optional body with context or rationale.
```

## Types

- `feat`: New feature or capability
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code restructuring without behavior change
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `chore`: Build, config, or tooling changes

## Rules

- One task = one commit. Do not batch multiple tasks into a single commit.
- Always reference the task ID from `tasks/CURRENT.md`.
- Write the subject in imperative mood ("add profile page" not "added profile page").
- Keep the subject under 72 characters.
